</table>

<div class="section-break"></div>

<h2>3. User Interface Demonstration & Data Entry Screens</h2>

<h3>3.1 All Pages & Navigation</h3>
<p>The system is split into two distinct applications based on specialized roles:</p>

<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Role</th>
            <th>Primary Pages</th>
            <th>Data Entry Components</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Customer</strong></td>
            <td>Home, Catalog, Product Details, Cart, Checkout, Profile, Orders, Custom Cake Designer.</td>
            <td>Login/Register forms, Custom Order Wizard, Payment Slip Upload, Feedback Forms.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Admin</strong></td>
            <td>Live Dashboard, Order Manager, Inventory (Cakes/Cats), Cashbook, Notifications, Settings.</td>
            <td>Add/Edit Cake Modal, Payment Approval Dialog, Notification Template Editor, Transaction Entry.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>3.2 Special Implementations</h3>

<h4>A. Frontend Validation:</h4>
<p>The system uses complex Regex patterns and state-based validation to ensure "Dirty Data" never reaches the server.</p>
<div class="code-snippet">
    // Example: Registration Validation Logic<br>
    email: !/^[A-Z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Z0-9.-]+\.[A-Z]{2,4}$/i.test(value)<br>
    password: /^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\d)(?=.*[@$!%*?&])[A-Za-z\d@$!%*?&]{8,}$/<br>
    phone: Must be exactly 10-15 digits based on international standards.
</div>

<h4>B. Backend Validation:</h4>
<p>Server-side logic re-verifies all critical business rules (Price integrity, Stock availability).</p>
<div class="code-snippet">
    // Example: Order Controller Validation<br>
    if (orderType === 'URGENT' && diffDays < 2) throw new Error("Urgent orders must be 48h lead time.");<br>
    if (loyaltyPointsRedeemed > customerPoints) return res.status(400).json({ error: "Insufficient Points" });
</div>

<h4>C. Security & Encryption:</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Bcrypt:</strong> Password data is salt-hashed (Cost=10) before database storage; raw passwords are never saved.</li>
    <li><strong>JWT (JSON Web Tokens):</strong> Used for stateless session management with 7-day expiration for customers and 1-day for admins.</li>
    <li><strong>OTP (One Time Password):</strong> Email-based 6-digit verification required for account activation.</li>
</ul>

<h4>D. Error Handling:</h4>
<p>Centralized error management ensures the app never crashes on production.</p>
<div class="code-snippet">
    // Global Error Boundary (Frontend) prevents "White Screen of Death"<br>
    // Try-Catch Middleware (Backend) returns formatted JSON errors with Status Codes: 401(Auth), 403(Role), 404(Missing).
</div>

<div class="section-break"></div>

<h2>4. Quality Assurance (QA) Methods Used</h2>
<p>To ensure 99.9% reliability, the following QA techniques were strictly followed:</p>

<ol>
    <li><strong>Rigorous Validation Testing:</strong> Each input field (Email, Price, Quantity) was tested with "Negative Data" (symbols, negative numbers, extremely long strings) to ensure graceful failure.</li>
    <li><strong>Manual Data Entry Audits:</strong> Admin records were manually entered and verified against the MySQL workbench to ensure mathematical accuracy in total calculations.</li>
    <li><strong>Browser Compatibility:</strong> The UI was tested in <strong>Chrome, Firefox, and Safari</strong> to ensure modern CSS (Flexbox/Grid) rendered consistently.</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile Responsiveness:</strong> Using Chrome DevTools and **physical mobile devices**, the "Mobile First" design for the customer site was verified for touch interactions.</li>
    <li><strong>Role Separation Testing:</strong> Attempting to access <code>/admin</code> URLs with a <code>CUSTOMER</code> account to verify the "PrivateRoute" security gates.</li>
    <li><strong>Scenario Testing:</strong> Simulating "Edge Cases" like placing a custom order exactly on the 2-day cutoff to verify timing logic.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>5. Reports Generated</h2>
<p>The system provides automated data outputs for business intelligence:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Revenue Reports:</strong> Daily, Weekly, and Monthly income summaries on the Admin Dashboard.</li>
    <li><strong>Daily Cashbook PDF/Audit:</strong> Summary of transactions with opening and closing balances.</li>
    <li><strong>Inventory Stock List:</strong> Automated reports on variant counts and category distribution.</li>
    <li><strong>Customer Feedback Logs:</strong> Aggregated ratings for quality control.</li>
</ul>

